<br>
The AC loss from the typically range item everyone has at 60, grodan's idol, hurts at times. Especially if your equipment is configed for healing on dragon raids, keep the magic 1250-1300AC gets tough. For example, I have horrid AC in shoulder(ODS), boots(haste boots), gaunts(coldain skin) and now range due to keeping wisdom/sta high. (Need to switch coldain skin to blessed mithril. Coldain were better than shining due to high wis/mana and HP gains from sta9 and hp20)<br>
<br>
My advise would be to use the idol of underking when fighting dragons/tov/SS and return the AC15 item when tanking/soloing since improved healing does not affect CC, our primary heal in solo/grinds.<br>
<br>
Only real problem I have with the idol is that I plan to get a good 2hb to be able to utilize the +5% 2hb range item I have in the bank to raise attack by 30 or so.  <p>Senchy Solariatus <BR>
